cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.GT 

This paper deals with cybersecurity and the Internet of Things (IoT), which are both relevant to the computer science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for cyber-physical attacks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of game theory to model botnet recruitment could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and the analysis of different mechanisms to deter botnet recruitment could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the focus on IoT devices and their vulnerabilities suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
